Why did they make Solomon's Temple?  It was a direction to look, to focus on, a special place for meditation, to do offerings, a community center, a home to God's beauty, that encouraged love of God. 
（是大卫想建造。他自己住在好房间里，也想为神造一个。但却是所罗门建造完成。赐平安者赐下平安给他。圣殿鼓励不了人爱神，反而是使人专注于圣殿的华丽外表。。。不过倒确实是成为了信仰生活的中心。毕竟，虽然鼓励不了人爱神，却是由爱神的人所建造的，充满了对神的爱。）
People cherished God's temple, beautifying it with gold and all fine things to show love of God(maybe just of gold), as great cathedrals were decorated with astounding, awe-striking intricate art and gargoyles, incredible devotion to God with hours of effort, toiling and slaving-away for the glory of God, for families with children to see stained-glass windows and tomes with ridiculously elaborate calligraphy to show love of God, from a people who did little else but show love toward God, lived in dire conditions by today's standards, yet with so much difficulty scraping-by, found the time to devote even all free-time to God!
